title: Idaho colleges roundup: Boise State women’s golf sixth in New Mexico
text:
Order a reprint of this story 
LAS CRUCES, N.M. — Senior McKenzie Ford led the Broncos with a tie for 10th place at the NM State Aggie Invitational on Wednesday. Ford fired a third-round score of 74 to finish at 3-over 219 on the NM State Golf Course. Boise State finished sixth in the 14-team field at 892 (28-over). BYU (859) won the event. 
COLLEGE OF IDAHO CROSS COUNTRY: Both Coyote squads are in the top 10 of the NAIA Coaches’ Poll, released Wednesday. The men matched their highest ranking in program history, climbing to No. 8 position (2005 and 2009), while the women jumped to No. 7 — their highest ranking since 2013, when they finished No. 2.
